==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wold
<hw>Wold</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>wold</ets>,
<ets>wald</ets>, AS. <ets>weald</ets>, <ets>wald</ets>, a wood, forest;
akin to OFries. & OS. <ets>wald</ets>, D. <ets>woud</ets>, G.
<ets>wald</ets>, Icel. <ets>v⟦oum⟧llr</ets>, a field, and probably to
Gr. <?/ a grove, Skr. <ets>v⟦amac⟧<?/a</ets> a garden, inclosure. Cf.
<er>Weald</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>A wood; a forest.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A plain, or low hill; a country without wood,
whether hilly or not.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And from his further bank Aetolia's <qex>wolds</qex> espied.</q>
<rj><qau>Byron.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The wind that beats the mountain, blows⟦br⟧
More softly round the open <qex>wold</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wold</ent>⟦br⟧

